description.narrative: National capacities enhanced to strengthen quality health and nutrition policy and legislation, particularly in target countries., which contributes to Child Health, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, children in the Pacific, particularly the most vulnerable, increasingly benefit from quality and resilient health and nutrition services and care practices.

description.narrative: The Vanuatu Public Expenditure Tracking Survey showed a stark under provision of capital resources dedicated to PHC facilities, with only 4 per cent of PHC facility expenditure attributable to MoH funding. More than 75 per cent of UNICEF's financing in three PICTs is incorporated within the MoH plan and budget, with significant improvements made in reducing UNICEF-specific transaction costs for MoHs. In Kiribati, the first role delineation policy, which defines the scope of the service package for health service provision, was finalized. At least 70 per cent of comprehensive multi-year plans (cMYPs) for immunization in three PICTs was implemented. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
